{"title_page": "Thoothukudi massacre", "text_new": "{{Infobox civilian attack\n| title       =Thoothukudi Massacare\n| image       = \n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| map         = {{Location map|Tamil Nadu|lat=8.48|long=78.04|caption=}}\n| map_caption = Location of Thoothukudi in Tamil Nadu\n| location    = [[Thoothukudi]], Tamil Nadu, [[India]]\n| target      = Protestors against [[Sterlite Copper]]\n| coordinates = {{Coord|8.784117|78.099142|display=inline,title}}\n| date        = 22 May 2018\n| time        = \n| timezone    = UTC+5:30\n| type        = [[Shooting]]<!-- Don't change without valid reference -->\n| fatalities  = 13<!-- Don't change without valid reference --><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india-sterlite-protest-live-updates-tuticorin-thoothukudi-death-toll-vedanta-copper-plant-443641 |title=Anti-Sterlite protests: 15 dead, 102 injured in Thoothukudi; electricity supply to Sterlite Industries cut off}}</ref>\n| injuries    = 102<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india-sterlite-protest-live-updates-tuticorin-thoothukudi-death-toll-vedanta-copper-plant-443641 |title=Anti-Sterlite protests: 13 dead, 102 injured in Thoothukudi; electricity supply to Sterlite Industries cut off}}</ref>\n| perps       = [[Tamil Nadu Police]] & Paramilitary forces\n| weapons     = [[L1A1 SLR]] [[battle rifle]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.vikatan.com/news/tamilnadu/125778-this-is-the-type-of-rifle-used-in-tuticorin.html |title=\u0ba4\u0bc2\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd 11 \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b89\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0ba4\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf \u0b87\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bcd}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/massacre-thoothukudi-intelligence-failure-or-deliberate-assault-81865 |title=The police firing in Thoothukudi: Intelligence failure or deliberate assault?}}</ref>\n| numparts    =\n}}\n\n[[File:Sterlitejpg.jpg|thumb|Protesters in large numbers take out a march against the Sterlite copper plant on May 22, 2018.]]The '''Thoothukudi police firing''' (also known as the '''Thoothukudi Massacre''' or '''Sterlite protest firing''') took place on 22 May 2018 in [[Thoothukudi]], [[Tamil Nadu]], India, when [[Tamil Nadu Police]] officers fired into a protest of 20,000 people.<ref name=\"financialexpress\" /> The protest was against the [[Sterlite Copper]] factory, which was accused of causing environmental pollution.<ref name=\"financialexpress\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.financialexpress.com/india-news/sterlite-protest-in-tuticorin-9-killed-in-tamil-nadu-top-developments-history-reasons-behind-violence/1177652/|title=Reasons behind Killings|last=|first=|date=|work=The Financial Express|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nSterlite Copper has been facing resistance from the local fishermen\u2019s groups in the area ever since the plant was given permission to be established by the J Jayalaitha AIADMK in 1993.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Sudhakar|first=P.|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/for-sterlite-its-crisis-situation-once-again/article4564893.ece|title=For Sterlite, it's crisis situation once again|date=2013-03-30|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-01|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> Sporadic protests have occurred in [[Thoothukudi]] since 1999, directed against the Sterlite Copper smelting works, the factory owned by [[Vedanta Limited]], a subsidiary of [[Vedanta Resources]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailyo.in/variety/sterlite-protests-sulphur-dioxide-vedanta-tamil-nadu/story/1/23101.html|title=Why hundreds of Tamils won't quit protests against Vedanta's Sterlite|website=www.dailyo.in|access-date=2018-05-28}}</ref> Protesters opposed the soil, water and air contamination caused by the factory.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|last=Narasimhan|first=T. E.|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/sterlite-s-pollution-problem-113041801267_1.html|title=Sterlite's pollution problem|date=2013-04-18|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n=== Pollution studies ===\nAn epidemiological study carried out by [[Tirunelveli Medical College]] in 2006\u201307 found an increased prevalence of respiratory diseases and ear, nose and throat (ENT) morbidity in the 5-km radius of Sterlite Industries. The study reported the prevalence of respiratory diseases in the area at 13.9% which was far higher than the state average. The prevalence of asthmatic bronchitis is 2.8%, which more than two-times the state average of 1.29%. Myalgia (general body pain) is another extensively reported symptom and women were often found to have menstrual disorders, like [[Menorrhagia|menorrhagiae]] and dysmenorrhagiae in the area.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/sterlite-here-s-proof-how-copper-plant-impacts-health-thoothukudi-people-78772|title=Sterlite - here\u2019s the proof: How the copper plant impacts health of Thoothukudi people|last=Jayaraman|first=Nityanand|date=April 1, 2018|website=thenewsminute.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> Their report blamed it on the air pollution caused by the industry's thermal power plants and automobiles in the area.<ref>{{cite book | last = Elango  | first = S. | title = Health status and Epidemiological study around 5&nbsp;km radius of Sterlite Industries (India) Limited, Thoothukudi | publisher = Tirunelveli Medical College | date = Oct 2008 | location = Tirunelveli | pages = 106 | language = English | url = https://poromboke.files.wordpress.com/2018/03/health-report-sterlite_edited.pdf}}</ref> The [[groundwater]] iron content in the area of the plant has been found to be 17\u201320 times the allowable limit, causing additional health problems for the population already experiencing higher than average incidence of respiratory diseases.<ref name=\"newsminute\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/sterlite-here-s-proof-how-copper-plant-impacts-health-thoothukudi-people-78772|title=Sterlite \u2013 here's the proof: How the copper plant impacts health of Thoothukudi people|date=2018-04-01|work=The News Minute|access-date=2018-05-22}}</ref> \n\nThe 1998 report by [[National Environmental Engineering Research Institute]] (NEERI), the levels of selenium, arsenic and lead in treated effluent were higher than prescribed standards. The team also found dead birds after they consumed the water mixed with the effluent. In another instance, the samples from a village 2-km northwest of the factory had levels of cadmium, copper, lead, chromium, and arsenic 2 to 9 times higher than allowed levels.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/sterlite-here-s-proof-data-how-smelter-likely-cause-water-pollution-79055|title=Sterlite \u2013 here\u2019s proof: The data on how the smelter is likely cause for water pollution|last=|first=|date=|website=www.thenewsminute.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2010, Sampling tests by an NGO Community Environmental Monitoring, found salinity level in an open well to be of 7854 mg/litre while levels exceeding 2000 mg/litre can badly damage the crops. Another water sample from a bore-well had sulfate levels ten-times higher than the average.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\nThe Tamil Nadu Pollution Control Board (TNPCB) observed that the unit has been releasing poisonous gas in the air. TNPCB identified that the sulphur dioxide levels went off the scale on the night of March 23, 2013. It showed a reading of 2939.55-mg/cubic meter against the decreed limit of 1250 mg/cubic meter.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailypioneer.com/2018/columnists/sterlite-protests-reach-a-climax.html|title=Sterlite protests reach a climax|last=Pioneer|first=The|website=The Pioneer|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 April 2018, the TNPCB accused the Sterlite Copper of causing groundwater pollution.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.downtoearth.org.in/news/governance/sterlite-typifies-all-that-s-wrong-with-environmental-governance-in-india-60877|title=Sterlite typifies all that's wrong with environmental governance in India|website=www.downtoearth.org.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n=== Gas leaks ===\nOn July 7th 1997, the Tamil Nadu Pollution Control Board told the company to shut down after a sulphur dioxide gas leak which hospitalized more than 90 people.<ref>{{Cite news|last=BSCAL|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/specials/sterlite-told-to-shut-plant-following-gas-leak-197070701041_1.html|title=Sterlite Told To Shut Plant Following Gas Leak|date=1997-07-07|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\nThe Sterlite Copper factory also made headlines in 2013 after a suspected sulphur dioxide gas leak from one of its smelter.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/sterlite-plant-idINDEE93005C20130401|title=Sterlite ordered to shut large copper smelter over 'gas leak'|date=2013-04-01|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-04-01|language=en}}</ref> The plant was blamed for health issues observed in the area related to gas leakage. Following the alleged gas leak in March 2013, the then chief minister, the late [[J. Jayalalithaa]], ordered its closure. The company appealed to the [[National Green Tribunal Act|National Green Tribunal]], which overturned the government order. The state moved the [[Supreme Court of India|Supreme Court]] against it, where the petition was still pending. The plant closed on March 27 of 2018, with the company citing a 15-day maintenance process.<ref name=\"financialexpress\" /> The Supreme Court ordered the company to pay a 100-crore fine for polluting the water, air and soil around the plant and the factory was temporarily shutdown by the pollution regulator.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/sc-slaps-rs-100-cr-penalty-on-sterlite-for-pollution/article4572805.ece|title=SC slaps Rs. 100 cr. penalty on Sterlite for pollution|last=Venkatesan|first=J.|date=2013-04-02|work=The Hindu|access-date=2018-05-28|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> About 150 people were arrested in protests against the plant.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nOn June 2019, the Tamil Nadu government reported that there were 84 incidents of gas leaks at Sterlite Copper in the year 2013 alone, to the [[Madras High Court]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/84-gas-leaks-at-sterlite-in-2013-alone-tn-tells-madras-hc/articleshow/69881981.cms|title=84 gas leaks at Sterlite in 2013 alone, Tamil Nadu tells Madras HC {{!}} Chennai News - Times of India|last=Jun 21|first=TNN {{!}} Updated:|last2=2019|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01|last3=Ist|first3=11:52}}</ref>\n\n=== Protests ===\nA wave of protests began on March 24, 2018 after the Sterlite Copper announced its plans to expand the plant, people around Kumarettiyapuram village protested for more than 100 days.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vikatan.com/news/tamilnadu/120896-after-kumarettiyapuram-pandarampatti-village-people-joins-sterlite-protest-in-thoothukudi.html|title=\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bb0\u0bc6\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bb8\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b9f\u0bcd \u0b86\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0bae\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bae\u0bcd|date=2018-04-01|work=Vikatan|access-date=2018-05-22|language=ta}}</ref> Later the Tamil Nadu Pollution Control Board rejected the application by the company for clearance. The protesters claimed that the company went on to expand despite the rejection by the government.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|last=Radhakrishnan|first=Sruthi|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/the-hindu-explains-sterlite-protests/article23969542.ece|title=The Hindu explains: Sterlite protests|date=2018-05-23|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-01|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> \n\nThe protesters wanted the company's smelting unit in Thoothukudi shut down as it was causing environmental damage to the area. The company has been accused of being negligent regarding environmental management, causing harm to the health of the locals in and around Thoothukudi.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n==Firing==\n\nOn May 22, 2018, thousands of people began to march to the district collector's office to submit a petition when the \"[[section 144]]\" was on implementation. Section 144 makes a gathering of more than four people as unlawful but an unofficial release said 20,000 people took out a procession towards the district-collector's office and the copper plant.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://india.ucanews.com/news/tuticorin-police-massacre-leaves-11-dead-priest-in-hospital/37364/daily|title=Tuticorin police massacre leaves 11 dead, christian priest Fr.Rev.Leo jayaseelan in hospital who was responsible for the little children and housewives from the church to larcilate the protests apart from the Urban naxals like \"Makkal Athigaram\"{{!}} UCAN India|website=india.ucanews.com|access-date=2018-05-28}}</ref> \n\nViolence broke out between the police and the protesters when the protesters moved to a four-road intersection close to the traffic sign on Palayamkottai Road.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Joseph|first=J. Praveen Paul|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/several-anti-sterlite-protesters-policemen-injured-in-thoothukudi/article23957774.ece|title=10 killed in police firing as anti-Sterlite rally turns violent in Thoothukudi|date=2018-05-22|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-01|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> The police started shooting at the protesters and were also accused of shooting without any formal warning.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/6-km-stir-ended-bloodshed-671436.html|title=A 6-km stir that ended in bloodshed|date=2018-05-23|access-date=2018-05-23|language=en}}</ref> Police were also reported of intentionally shooting at the heads of the protesters.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/police-targeted-protesters-shot-head-victims-families-671547.html|title=Police targeted the protesters; shot at head|date=2018-05-24|access-date=2018-05-24|language=en}}</ref> 13 protesters were killed including a 17-year old school student, and dozens were injured.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/she-wanted-be-lawyer-her-dreams-lie-box-thoothukudi-teen-victim-s-kin-81854|title=She wanted to be a lawyer, her dreams lie in a box|date=2018-05-24|access-date=2018-05-24|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"fivedays\" /><ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/as-tuticorin-weeps-for-13-felled-in-police-firing-a-quite-rage-persists/articleshow/64334132.cms</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://zeenews.india.com/tamil-nadu/tamil-nadu-police-fired-from-assault-rifles-on-anti-sterlite-protesters-heard-saying-at-least-one-should-die-2110643.html|title=Tamil Nadu Police fired from assault rifles on anti-Sterlite protesters, heard saying at least one should die{{!}} Zee News India|website=zeenews.india.com|access-date=2018-06-02}}</ref>\n\nFIRs filed in local police stations, claimed that the order to shoot was issued by officers in the rank of deputy Tehsildars and people pointed out that only Collectors have the authority to issue shooting orders.<ref name=\"TH20180529-1\">{{cite news | last = Pon Vasanth | first = B. A | title = Three officers in the rank of deputy tahsildar issued firing orders in Thoothukudi, say FIRs | newspaper = The Hindu | location = Madurai | language = English | publisher = The Hindu Group | date = 29 May 2018 | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/3-deputy-tahsildars-issued-firing-orders-say-firs/article24017934.ece | access-date = 30 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe Tamil Nadu government ordered a shutdown of Internet in the entire districts of Tuticorin, Tirunelveli and Kanyakumari for five days after the firing.<ref name=\"fivedays\">{{cite web |title=Sterlite protest: Tamil Nadu orders internet suspension for five days in three southern districts |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil-nadu/2018/may/23/sterlite-protest-tamil-nadu-orders-internet-suspension-for-five-days-in-three-southern-districts-1818574.html |website=New Indian Express |accessdate=9 July 2018 |date=23 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Reactions==\n\n* [[Thirumurugan Gandhi]], the coordinator of [[May 17 Movement]], took the issue to the 38th session of the [[United Nations Human Rights Council]], Geneva in July 2018. On 9 August 2018, Thirumurugan Gandhi was detained by immigration authorities at Bangalore Airport on his return to India and charged under Section 124 A (sedition), 153 A (1) and 153 (b) of IPC for speaking about the Thoothukudi firings at the UNHRC. Court, later, refused to remand him under judicial custody as it found the charges are baseless.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/court-refuses-detain-activist-thirumurugan-gandhi-86351|title=Court refuses to detain activist Thirumurugan Gandhi|date=2018-08-10|work=The News Minute|access-date=2018-08-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/2018/aug/10/thirumurugan-gandhi-held-in-bengaluru-for-un-speech-on-police-firing-in-thoothukudi-1855732.html|title=Thirumurugan Gandhi held in Bengaluru for UN speech on police firing in Thoothukudi|work=The New Indian Express|access-date=2018-08-28}}</ref>\n* [[Indian National Congress]] party president [[Rahul Gandhi]] described it as \"[[state-sponsored terrorism]]\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://zeenews.india.com/india/anti-sterlite-protest-gunning-down-9-people-by-police-in-tamil-nadu-is-state-sponsored-terrorism-says-rahul-gandhi-2110523.html?src=fb|title=Anti-Sterlite protest: Gunning down 9 people by police in Tamil Nadu is state-sponsored terrorism, says Rahul Gandhi|date=2018-05-22|work=Zee News|access-date=2018-05-22|language=en}}</ref> \n*[[Seeman (politician)|Seeman]] condemned the firing, and his political party held a rally in Tirunelveli condemning the shooting.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://tamil.oneindia.com/news/tamilnadu/seeman-condemns-the-gun-firing-at-thoothukudi-protest/articlecontent-pf308746-320470.html|title=Naam Thamizhar Katchi leader Seeman condemns gun firing at Thoothukudi|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=2018-05-31}}</ref>\n* [[Kamal Haasan]] was one of the first political leaders to arrive to Tuticorin to see the injured in the hospital, after the shootings.\n* [[Vaiko]] and [[M.K.Stalin]] demanded investigations into the shootings.<ref>http://indianexpress.com/article/india/mass-murder-of-innocent-people-dmks-stalin-questions-order-to-fire-at-anti-sterlite-protesters-5187874/</ref>\n* [[National Human Rights Commission of India]] demanded investigation into the killings.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2018/05/indian-police-accused-killing-11-protesters-180523134721427.html |title=Indian police accused of killing at least 11 protesters}}</ref> It asked its Director General (Investigation) to send a team headed by an [[Superintendent of Police|SP]] to visit the spot and conduct an inquiry.<ref name=\"TH20180530-1\" />\n* Tamils and [[Tamil diaspora]] across the world including [[United States]], [[Canada]], [[Europe]], [[Malaysia]], [[Sri Lanka]] and [[Australia]] held protests against the killing.\n* In support of the protests The UK's Opposition, Labour Party, has called for Vedanta to be delisted from the London Stock Exchange. [[John McDonnell]], the UK's Shadow Chancellor, said removing Vedanta Resources from the London financial markets would prevent reputational damage from the \"rogue\" company which has been operating \"illegal\" mining concerns for years. \"After the firing on the protestors this week, regulators must now take action. Vedanta must be immediately delisted from the London Stock Exchange to remove its cloak of respectability, restore confidence in the governance of the Stock Exchange, and prevent further reputational damage to London's financial markets from this rogue corporation,\" McDonnell said in a statement.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/uk-opposition-wants-vedanta-delisted-from-london-stock-exchange/articleshow/64331300.cms |title=UK Opposition wants Vedanta delisted on London Stock Exchange}}</ref>\n* Actor [[Rajinikanth]] said \"anti-social elements\" in the crowd had to be \"dealt with an iron hand\" and also stated that Tamil Nadu will become a graveyard  if the people of the state continue to protest.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-44313804|title=Rajinikanth: Anger after actor justifies deadly police firing|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/rajinikanth-blames-anti-social-elements-for-sterlite-protest201805302030500001/ |title=Rajinikanth blames anti-social elements for Sterlite protest}}</ref> His reaction to the firing was criticized on the social media.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-superstar-rajinikanth-apologises-for-losing-cool-at-media-interaction-2621031 |title=Superstar Rajinikanth apologises for losing cool at media interaction |access-date=3 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/rajinikanth-s-speech-earns-him-negative-image-on-social-media-news-tamil-sf5jD6fcigihb.html|title=Rajinikanth's speech earns him negative image on social media?|access-date=3 June 2018}}</ref> Following his controversial statements regarding the Thoothukudi shooting scandal, the Tamil activist groups in [[Norway]] and [[Switzerland]] banned the release of Rajinikanth's film [[Kaala (2018 film)|''Kaala'']] in Norway and Switzerland by the scheduled world wide release date as of 7 June.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tamil.news18.com/news/entertainment/after-norway-kaala-ban-in-swiss-too-24491.html|title=\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bbe \u0baa\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0b9f \u0bae\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u2013 News18 Tamil|website=News18 Tamil|access-date=2018-06-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://tamil.samayam.com/tamil-cinema/movie-news/rajinikanth-kaala-movie-banned-in-switzerland-and-norway/articleshow/64428551.cms|title=\u0bb0\u0b9c\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc7, \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bbe \u0baa\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc8 - Samayam Tamil|date=2018-06-02|work=[[Samayam Tamil]]|access-date=2018-06-03|language=ta}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/foreign-nations-ban-rajinis-kaala-tamil-news-214931|title=Foreign nations ban Rajini's 'Kaala'? - Tamil Movie News \u2013 IndiaGlitz.com|work=IndiaGlitz.com|access-date=2018-06-03}}</ref> The Tamil diaspora groups in Norway and Switzerland announced that they would not release the films of actors in the future who deliberately hurt the feelings and attitudes of Tamil people following the comments from Rajinikanth on Tamils.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tamilnews.com/2018/06/01/switzerland-ban-super-star-movie-following-norway/|title=\u0ba8\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0bb8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd '\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bbe' \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc8??|last=S|first=Ashwiniya|date=2018-06-01|work=TAMIL NEWS|access-date=2018-06-03|language=en-US}}</ref> However, the ban was later on lifted and the film was released within a week, a day before the scheduled worldwide release in Switzerland and Norway.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.topkino.ch/pdf/Programm24.pdf|title=Wochenprogramm|date=2018-06-11|work=Top Kino|access-date=2018-06-19|language=de-CH|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619085834/http://www.topkino.ch/pdf/Programm24.pdf|archivedate=2018-06-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.filmweb.no/film/article1361077.ece|title=Kaala (Tamil)|date=2018-06-01|work=Filmweb|access-date=2018-06-19|language=no-NO|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619090401/https://www.filmweb.no/film/article1361077.ece|archivedate=2018-06-19}}</ref>\n\nA video released by the environmental activist S. Mugilan, a few days before he went missing from a train while travelling from Chennai to Madurai, said that the \"shooting was well planned\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/rights/environmental-activist-missing-thoothukudi-massacre-police|title=Activist Goes Missing Hours After Incriminating Top Cops in Thoothukudi Massacre|website=The Wire|access-date=2019-03-20}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=TuNo|title=Arsonists - Sterlite - The Hidden Truth - \u0b95\u0bca\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd? \u0bb8\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b9f\u0bcd - \u0bae\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0b89\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd|date=2019-02-08|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SlukGKrzYLc|access-date=2019-03-20}}</ref>\n\n== Government response ==\nOn 28 May 2018, the Sterlite factory was sealed after an order given by the Tamil Nadu Environmental pollution and Forests Department.<ref name=\"TH20180528-1\">{{cite news | last = Rohit | first = T. K. | title = Sterlite Copper to be permanently closed, says Tamil Nadu government | newspaper = The Hindu | location = Chennai | language = English | publisher = The Hindu Group | date = 28 May 2018 | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/sterlite-copper-to-be-permanently-closed-says-tamil-nadu-government/article24014605.ece | access-date = 30 May 2018}}</ref> The next day, Tamil Nadu's State Industries Promotion Corporation (SIPCOT) announced that it would take back 342.22 acres of land that it had given for expansion of the facility.<ref name=\"TH20180530-1\">{{cite news | title = T.N. to take back land allotted to Sterlite | newspaper = The Hindu | location = Chennai / New Delhi | language = English | publisher = The Hindu Group | date = 30 May 2018 | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/tn-to-take-back-land-allotted-to-sterlite/article24029865.ece | access-date = 30 May 2018}}</ref> Many political leaders including [[M.K.Stalin]], [[Seeman (politician)|Seeman]] and [[Anbumani Ramadoss]] criticized the sealing order, saying that it would not stand up to legal scrutiny since the government had given no reason for shutting down the factory.<ref name=\"TH20180530-2\">{{cite news | title = G.O. won't stand up to legal scrutiny: Stalin | newspaper = The Hindu | location = Chennai | language = English | publisher = The Hindu Group | date = 30 May 2018 | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/go-wont-stand-up-to-legal-scrutiny-stalin/article24027956.ece | access-date = 30 May 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"TH20180530-3\">{{cite news | title = G.O. to close Sterlite plant inadequate | newspaper = The Hindu | location = Chennai | language = English | publisher = The Hindu Group | date = 30 May 2018 | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/go-to-close-sterlite-plant-inadequate/article24030059.ece | access-date = 30 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Aftermath ==\nOn October 28, 2018, the Tamil Nadu Pollution Control Board reported that the sulphur-dioxide levels in the air had reduced significantly after the Sterlite plant's closure.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/national/so2-levels-have-reduced-significantly-after-closure-of-sterlite-plant-tnpcb/article25353938.ece|title=SO2 levels have reduced significantly after closure of Sterlite plant: TNPCB|last=Simhan|first=TE Raja|website=@businessline|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\nOn November 2019, the Tamil Nadu Pollution Control Board reported that the [[Ambient air quality criteria|ambient air quality]] had improved dramatically after the closure of the plant.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/environment/tuticorin-air-quality-aqi-sterlite-copper-smelting-pollution-sipcot-tnpcb|title=Tuticorin Air Quality Improves Noticeably After Sterlite Closure: TNPCB Data|website=The Wire|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Manjolai Labourers massacre]]\n* [[2018 Tamil Nadu protests for Kaveri water sharing]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Pollution in India]]\n[[Category:Police brutality in India]]\n[[Category:2018 in Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:2018 murders in Asia]]\n[[Category:May 2018 crimes in Asia|Thoothukudi_firing]]\n[[Category:Thoothukudi]]\n[[Category:Protests in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox civilian attack\n| title       =Thoothukudi Massacare\n| image       = \n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| map         = {{Location map|Tamil Nadu|lat=8.48|long=78.04|caption=}}\n| map_caption = Location of Thoothukudi in Tamil Nadu\n| location    = [[Thoothukudi]], Tamil Nadu, [[India]]\n| target      = Protestors against [[Sterlite Copper]]\n| coordinates = {{Coord|8.784117|78.099142|display=inline,title}}\n| date        = 22 May 2018\n| time        = \n| timezone    = UTC+5:30\n| type        = [[Shooting]]<!-- Don't change without valid reference -->\n| fatalities  = 13<!-- Don't change without valid reference --><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india-sterlite-protest-live-updates-tuticorin-thoothukudi-death-toll-vedanta-copper-plant-443641 |title=Anti-Sterlite protests: 15 dead, 102 injured in Thoothukudi; electricity supply to Sterlite Industries cut off}}</ref>\n| injuries    = 102<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india-sterlite-protest-live-updates-tuticorin-thoothukudi-death-toll-vedanta-copper-plant-443641 |title=Anti-Sterlite protests: 13 dead, 102 injured in Thoothukudi; electricity supply to Sterlite Industries cut off}}</ref>\n| perps       = [[Tamil Nadu Police]] & Paramilitary forces\n| weapons     = [[L1A1 SLR]] [[battle rifle]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.vikatan.com/news/tamilnadu/125778-this-is-the-type-of-rifle-used-in-tuticorin.html |title=\u0ba4\u0bc2\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd 11 \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b89\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0ba4\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf \u0b87\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bcd}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/massacre-thoothukudi-intelligence-failure-or-deliberate-assault-81865 |title=The police firing in Thoothukudi: Intelligence failure or deliberate assault?}}</ref>\n| numparts    =\n}}\n\n[[File:Sterlitejpg.jpg|thumb|Protesters in large numbers take out a march against the Sterlite copper plant on May 22, 2018.]]The '''Thoothukudi police firing''' (also known as the '''Thoothukudi Massacre''' or '''Sterlite protest firing''') took place on 22 May 2018 in [[Thoothukudi]], [[Tamil Nadu]], India, when [[Tamil Nadu Police]] officers fired into a protest of 20,000 people.<ref name=\"financialexpress\" /> The protest was against the [[Sterlite Copper]] factory, which was accused of causing environmental pollution.<ref name=\"financialexpress\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.financialexpress.com/india-news/sterlite-protest-in-tuticorin-9-killed-in-tamil-nadu-top-developments-history-reasons-behind-violence/1177652/|title=Reasons behind Killings|last=|first=|date=|work=The Financial Express|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nSterlite Copper has been facing resistance from the local fishermen\u2019s groups in the area ever since the plant was given permission to be established by the J Jayalaitha AIADMK in 1993.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Sudhakar|first=P.|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/for-sterlite-its-crisis-situation-once-again/article4564893.ece|title=For Sterlite, it's crisis situation once again|date=2013-03-30|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-01|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> Sporadic protests have occurred in [[Thoothukudi]] since 1999, directed against the Sterlite Copper smelting works, the factory owned by [[Vedanta Limited]], a subsidiary of [[Vedanta Resources]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailyo.in/variety/sterlite-protests-sulphur-dioxide-vedanta-tamil-nadu/story/1/23101.html|title=Why hundreds of Tamils won't quit protests against Vedanta's Sterlite|website=www.dailyo.in|access-date=2018-05-28}}</ref> Protesters opposed the soil, water and air contamination caused by the factory.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|last=Narasimhan|first=T. E.|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/sterlite-s-pollution-problem-113041801267_1.html|title=Sterlite's pollution problem|date=2013-04-18|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n=== Pollution studies ===\nAn epidemiological study carried out by [[Tirunelveli Medical College]] in 2006\u201307 found an increased prevalence of respiratory diseases and ear, nose and throat (ENT) morbidity in the 5-km radius of Sterlite Industries. The study reported the prevalence of respiratory diseases in the area at 13.9% which was far higher than the state average. The prevalence of asthmatic bronchitis is 2.8%, which more than two-times the state average of 1.29%. Myalgia (general body pain) is another extensively reported symptom and women were often found to have menstrual disorders, like [[Menorrhagia|menorrhagiae]] and dysmenorrhagiae in the area.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/sterlite-here-s-proof-how-copper-plant-impacts-health-thoothukudi-people-78772|title=Sterlite - here\u2019s the proof: How the copper plant impacts health of Thoothukudi people|last=Jayaraman|first=Nityanand|date=April 1, 2018|website=thenewsminute.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> Their report blamed it on the air pollution caused by the industry's thermal power plants and automobiles in the area.<ref>{{cite book | last = Elango  | first = S. | title = Health status and Epidemiological study around 5&nbsp;km radius of Sterlite Industries (India) Limited, Thoothukudi | publisher = Tirunelveli Medical College | date = Oct 2008 | location = Tirunelveli | pages = 106 | language = English | url = https://poromboke.files.wordpress.com/2018/03/health-report-sterlite_edited.pdf}}</ref> The [[groundwater]] iron content in the area of the plant has been found to be 17\u201320 times the allowable limit, causing additional health problems for the population already experiencing higher than average incidence of respiratory diseases.<ref name=\"newsminute\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/sterlite-here-s-proof-how-copper-plant-impacts-health-thoothukudi-people-78772|title=Sterlite \u2013 here's the proof: How the copper plant impacts health of Thoothukudi people|date=2018-04-01|work=The News Minute|access-date=2018-05-22}}</ref> \n\nThe 1998 report by [[National Environmental Engineering Research Institute]] (NEERI), the levels of selenium, arsenic and lead in treated effluent were higher than prescribed standards. The team also found dead birds after they consumed the water mixed with the effluent. In another instance, the samples from a a village 2-km northwest of the factory had levels of cadmium, copper, lead, chromium, and arsenic 2 to 9 times higher than allowed levels.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/sterlite-here-s-proof-data-how-smelter-likely-cause-water-pollution-79055|title=Sterlite \u2013 here\u2019s proof: The data on how the smelter is likely cause for water pollution|last=|first=|date=|website=www.thenewsminute.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2010, Sampling tests by an NGO Community Environmental Monitoring, found salinity level in an open well to be of 7854 mg/litre while levels exceeding 2000 mg/litre can badly damage the crops. Another water sample from a bore-well had sulfate levels ten-times higher than the average.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\nThe Tamil Nadu Pollution Control Board (TNPCB) observed that the unit has been releasing poisonous gas in the air. TNPCB identified that the sulphur dioxide levels went off the scale on the night of March 23, 2013. It showed a reading of 2939.55-mg/cubic meter against the decreed limit of 1250 mg/cubic meter.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailypioneer.com/2018/columnists/sterlite-protests-reach-a-climax.html|title=Sterlite protests reach a climax|last=Pioneer|first=The|website=The Pioneer|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 April 2018, the TNPCB accused the Sterlite Copper of causing groundwater pollution.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.downtoearth.org.in/news/governance/sterlite-typifies-all-that-s-wrong-with-environmental-governance-in-india-60877|title=Sterlite typifies all that's wrong with environmental governance in India|website=www.downtoearth.org.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n=== Gas leaks ===\nOn July 7th 1997, the Tamil Nadu Pollution Control Board told the company to shut down after a sulphur dioxide gas leak which hospitalized more than 90 people.<ref>{{Cite news|last=BSCAL|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/specials/sterlite-told-to-shut-plant-following-gas-leak-197070701041_1.html|title=Sterlite Told To Shut Plant Following Gas Leak|date=1997-07-07|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\nThe Sterlite Copper factory also made headlines in 2013 after a suspected sulphur dioxide gas leak from one of its smelter.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/sterlite-plant-idINDEE93005C20130401|title=Sterlite ordered to shut large copper smelter over 'gas leak'|date=2013-04-01|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-04-01|language=en}}</ref> The plant was blamed for health issues observed in the area related to gas leakage. Following the alleged gas leak in March 2013, the then chief minister, the late [[J. Jayalalithaa]], ordered its closure. The company appealed to the [[National Green Tribunal Act|National Green Tribunal]], which overturned the government order. The state moved the [[Supreme Court of India|Supreme Court]] against it, where the petition was still pending. The plant closed on March 27 of 2018, with the company citing a 15-day maintenance process.<ref name=\"financialexpress\" /> The Supreme Court ordered the company to pay a 100-crore fine for polluting the water, air and soil around the plant and the factory was temporarily shutdown by the pollution regulator.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/sc-slaps-rs-100-cr-penalty-on-sterlite-for-pollution/article4572805.ece|title=SC slaps Rs. 100 cr. penalty on Sterlite for pollution|last=Venkatesan|first=J.|date=2013-04-02|work=The Hindu|access-date=2018-05-28|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> About 150 people were arrested in protests against the plant.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nOn June 2019, the Tamil Nadu government reported that there were 84 incidents of gas leaks at Sterlite Copper in the year 2013 alone, to the [[Madras High Court]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/84-gas-leaks-at-sterlite-in-2013-alone-tn-tells-madras-hc/articleshow/69881981.cms|title=84 gas leaks at Sterlite in 2013 alone, Tamil Nadu tells Madras HC {{!}} Chennai News - Times of India|last=Jun 21|first=TNN {{!}} Updated:|last2=2019|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01|last3=Ist|first3=11:52}}</ref>\n\n=== Protests ===\nA wave of protests began on March 24, 2018 after the Sterlite Copper announced its plans to expand the plant, people around Kumarettiyapuram village protested for more than 100 days.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vikatan.com/news/tamilnadu/120896-after-kumarettiyapuram-pandarampatti-village-people-joins-sterlite-protest-in-thoothukudi.html|title=\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bb0\u0bc6\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bb8\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b9f\u0bcd \u0b86\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0bae\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bae\u0bcd|date=2018-04-01|work=Vikatan|access-date=2018-05-22|language=ta}}</ref> Later the Tamil Nadu Pollution Control Board rejected the application by the company for clearance. The protesters claimed that the company went on to expand despite the rejection by the government.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|last=Radhakrishnan|first=Sruthi|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/the-hindu-explains-sterlite-protests/article23969542.ece|title=The Hindu explains: Sterlite protests|date=2018-05-23|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-01|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> \n\nThe protesters wanted the company's smelting unit in Thoothukudi shut down as it was causing environmental damage to the area. The company has been accused of being negligent regarding environmental management, causing harm to the health of the locals in and around Thoothukudi.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n==Firing==\n\nOn May 22, 2018, thousands of people began to march to the district collector's office to submit a petition when the \"[[section 144]]\" was on implementation. Section 144 makes a gathering of more than four people as unlawful but an unofficial release said 20,000 people took out a procession towards the district-collector's office and the copper plant.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://india.ucanews.com/news/tuticorin-police-massacre-leaves-11-dead-priest-in-hospital/37364/daily|title=Tuticorin police massacre leaves 11 dead, christian priest Fr.Rev.Leo jayaseelan in hospital who was responsible for the little children and housewives from the church to larcilate the protests apart from the Urban naxals like \"Makkal Athigaram\"{{!}} UCAN India|website=india.ucanews.com|access-date=2018-05-28}}</ref> \n\nViolence broke out between the police and the protesters when the protesters moved to a four-road intersection close to the traffic sign on Palayamkottai Road.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Joseph|first=J. Praveen Paul|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/several-anti-sterlite-protesters-policemen-injured-in-thoothukudi/article23957774.ece|title=10 killed in police firing as anti-Sterlite rally turns violent in Thoothukudi|date=2018-05-22|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-01|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> The police started shooting at the protesters and were also accused of shooting without any formal warning.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/6-km-stir-ended-bloodshed-671436.html|title=A 6-km stir that ended in bloodshed|date=2018-05-23|access-date=2018-05-23|language=en}}</ref> Police were also reported of intentionally shooting at the heads of the protesters.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/police-targeted-protesters-shot-head-victims-families-671547.html|title=Police targeted the protesters; shot at head|date=2018-05-24|access-date=2018-05-24|language=en}}</ref> 13 protesters were killed including a 17-year old school student, and dozens were injured.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/she-wanted-be-lawyer-her-dreams-lie-box-thoothukudi-teen-victim-s-kin-81854|title=She wanted to be a lawyer, her dreams lie in a box|date=2018-05-24|access-date=2018-05-24|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"fivedays\" /><ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/as-tuticorin-weeps-for-13-felled-in-police-firing-a-quite-rage-persists/articleshow/64334132.cms</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://zeenews.india.com/tamil-nadu/tamil-nadu-police-fired-from-assault-rifles-on-anti-sterlite-protesters-heard-saying-at-least-one-should-die-2110643.html|title=Tamil Nadu Police fired from assault rifles on anti-Sterlite protesters, heard saying at least one should die{{!}} Zee News India|website=zeenews.india.com|access-date=2018-06-02}}</ref>\n\nFIRs filed in local police stations, claimed that the order to shoot was issued by officers in the rank of deputy Tehsildars and people pointed out that only Collectors have the authority to issue shooting orders.<ref name=\"TH20180529-1\">{{cite news | last = Pon Vasanth | first = B. A | title = Three officers in the rank of deputy tahsildar issued firing orders in Thoothukudi, say FIRs | newspaper = The Hindu | location = Madurai | language = English | publisher = The Hindu Group | date = 29 May 2018 | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/3-deputy-tahsildars-issued-firing-orders-say-firs/article24017934.ece | access-date = 30 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe Tamil Nadu government ordered a shutdown of Internet in the entire districts of Tuticorin, Tirunelveli and Kanyakumari for five days after the firing.<ref name=\"fivedays\">{{cite web |title=Sterlite protest: Tamil Nadu orders internet suspension for five days in three southern districts |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil-nadu/2018/may/23/sterlite-protest-tamil-nadu-orders-internet-suspension-for-five-days-in-three-southern-districts-1818574.html |website=New Indian Express |accessdate=9 July 2018 |date=23 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Reactions==\n\n* [[Thirumurugan Gandhi]], the coordinator of [[May 17 Movement]], took the issue to the 38th session of the [[United Nations Human Rights Council]], Geneva in July 2018. On 9 August 2018, Thirumurugan Gandhi was detained by immigration authorities at Bangalore Airport on his return to India and charged under Section 124 A (sedition), 153 A (1) and 153 (b) of IPC for speaking about the Thoothukudi firings at the UNHRC. Court, later, refused to remand him under judicial custody as it found the charges are baseless.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/court-refuses-detain-activist-thirumurugan-gandhi-86351|title=Court refuses to detain activist Thirumurugan Gandhi|date=2018-08-10|work=The News Minute|access-date=2018-08-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/2018/aug/10/thirumurugan-gandhi-held-in-bengaluru-for-un-speech-on-police-firing-in-thoothukudi-1855732.html|title=Thirumurugan Gandhi held in Bengaluru for UN speech on police firing in Thoothukudi|work=The New Indian Express|access-date=2018-08-28}}</ref>\n* [[Indian National Congress]] party president [[Rahul Gandhi]] described it as \"[[state-sponsored terrorism]]\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://zeenews.india.com/india/anti-sterlite-protest-gunning-down-9-people-by-police-in-tamil-nadu-is-state-sponsored-terrorism-says-rahul-gandhi-2110523.html?src=fb|title=Anti-Sterlite protest: Gunning down 9 people by police in Tamil Nadu is state-sponsored terrorism, says Rahul Gandhi|date=2018-05-22|work=Zee News|access-date=2018-05-22|language=en}}</ref> \n*[[Seeman (politician)|Seeman]] condemned the firing, and his political party held a rally in Tirunelveli condemning the shooting.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://tamil.oneindia.com/news/tamilnadu/seeman-condemns-the-gun-firing-at-thoothukudi-protest/articlecontent-pf308746-320470.html|title=Naam Thamizhar Katchi leader Seeman condemns gun firing at Thoothukudi|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=2018-05-31}}</ref>\n* [[Kamal Haasan]] was one of the first political leaders to arrive to Tuticorin to see the injured in the hospital, after the shootings.\n* [[Vaiko]] and [[M.K.Stalin]] demanded investigations into the shootings.<ref>http://indianexpress.com/article/india/mass-murder-of-innocent-people-dmks-stalin-questions-order-to-fire-at-anti-sterlite-protesters-5187874/</ref>\n* [[National Human Rights Commission of India]] demanded investigation into the killings.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2018/05/indian-police-accused-killing-11-protesters-180523134721427.html |title=Indian police accused of killing at least 11 protesters}}</ref> It asked its Director General (Investigation) to send a team headed by an [[Superintendent of Police|SP]] to visit the spot and conduct an inquiry.<ref name=\"TH20180530-1\" />\n* Tamils and [[Tamil diaspora]] across the world including [[United States]], [[Canada]], [[Europe]], [[Malaysia]], [[Sri Lanka]] and [[Australia]] held protests against the killing.\n* In support of the protests The UK's Opposition, Labour Party, has called for Vedanta to be delisted from the London Stock Exchange. [[John McDonnell]], the UK's Shadow Chancellor, said removing Vedanta Resources from the London financial markets would prevent reputational damage from the \"rogue\" company which has been operating \"illegal\" mining concerns for years. \"After the firing on the protestors this week, regulators must now take action. Vedanta must be immediately delisted from the London Stock Exchange to remove its cloak of respectability, restore confidence in the governance of the Stock Exchange, and prevent further reputational damage to London's financial markets from this rogue corporation,\" McDonnell said in a statement.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/uk-opposition-wants-vedanta-delisted-from-london-stock-exchange/articleshow/64331300.cms |title=UK Opposition wants Vedanta delisted on London Stock Exchange}}</ref>\n* Actor [[Rajinikanth]] said \"anti-social elements\" in the crowd had to be \"dealt with an iron hand\" and also stated that Tamil Nadu will become a graveyard  if the people of the state continue to protest.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-44313804|title=Rajinikanth: Anger after actor justifies deadly police firing|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/rajinikanth-blames-anti-social-elements-for-sterlite-protest201805302030500001/ |title=Rajinikanth blames anti-social elements for Sterlite protest}}</ref> His reaction to the firing was criticized on the social media.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-superstar-rajinikanth-apologises-for-losing-cool-at-media-interaction-2621031 |title=Superstar Rajinikanth apologises for losing cool at media interaction |access-date=3 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/rajinikanth-s-speech-earns-him-negative-image-on-social-media-news-tamil-sf5jD6fcigihb.html|title=Rajinikanth's speech earns him negative image on social media?|access-date=3 June 2018}}</ref> Following his controversial statements regarding the Thoothukudi shooting scandal, the Tamil activist groups in [[Norway]] and [[Switzerland]] banned the release of Rajinikanth's film [[Kaala (2018 film)|''Kaala'']] in Norway and Switzerland by the scheduled world wide release date as of 7 June.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tamil.news18.com/news/entertainment/after-norway-kaala-ban-in-swiss-too-24491.html|title=\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bbe \u0baa\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0b9f \u0bae\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u2013 News18 Tamil|website=News18 Tamil|access-date=2018-06-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://tamil.samayam.com/tamil-cinema/movie-news/rajinikanth-kaala-movie-banned-in-switzerland-and-norway/articleshow/64428551.cms|title=\u0bb0\u0b9c\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc7, \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bbe \u0baa\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc8 - Samayam Tamil|date=2018-06-02|work=[[Samayam Tamil]]|access-date=2018-06-03|language=ta}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/foreign-nations-ban-rajinis-kaala-tamil-news-214931|title=Foreign nations ban Rajini's 'Kaala'? - Tamil Movie News \u2013 IndiaGlitz.com|work=IndiaGlitz.com|access-date=2018-06-03}}</ref> The Tamil diaspora groups in Norway and Switzerland announced that they would not release the films of actors in the future who deliberately hurt the feelings and attitudes of Tamil people following the comments from Rajinikanth on Tamils.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tamilnews.com/2018/06/01/switzerland-ban-super-star-movie-following-norway/|title=\u0ba8\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0bb8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd '\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bbe' \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc8??|last=S|first=Ashwiniya|date=2018-06-01|work=TAMIL NEWS|access-date=2018-06-03|language=en-US}}</ref> However, the ban was later on lifted and the film was released within a week, a day before the scheduled worldwide release in Switzerland and Norway.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.topkino.ch/pdf/Programm24.pdf|title=Wochenprogramm|date=2018-06-11|work=Top Kino|access-date=2018-06-19|language=de-CH|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619085834/http://www.topkino.ch/pdf/Programm24.pdf|archivedate=2018-06-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.filmweb.no/film/article1361077.ece|title=Kaala (Tamil)|date=2018-06-01|work=Filmweb|access-date=2018-06-19|language=no-NO|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619090401/https://www.filmweb.no/film/article1361077.ece|archivedate=2018-06-19}}</ref>\n\nA video released by the environmental activist S. Mugilan, a few days before he went missing from a train while travelling from Chennai to Madurai, said that the \"shooting was well planned\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/rights/environmental-activist-missing-thoothukudi-massacre-police|title=Activist Goes Missing Hours After Incriminating Top Cops in Thoothukudi Massacre|website=The Wire|access-date=2019-03-20}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=TuNo|title=Arsonists - Sterlite - The Hidden Truth - \u0b95\u0bca\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd? \u0bb8\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b9f\u0bcd - \u0bae\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0b89\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd|date=2019-02-08|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SlukGKrzYLc|access-date=2019-03-20}}</ref>\n\n== Government response ==\nOn 28 May 2018, the Sterlite factory was sealed after an order given by the Tamil Nadu Environmental pollution and Forests Department.<ref name=\"TH20180528-1\">{{cite news | last = Rohit | first = T. K. | title = Sterlite Copper to be permanently closed, says Tamil Nadu government | newspaper = The Hindu | location = Chennai | language = English | publisher = The Hindu Group | date = 28 May 2018 | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/sterlite-copper-to-be-permanently-closed-says-tamil-nadu-government/article24014605.ece | access-date = 30 May 2018}}</ref> The next day, Tamil Nadu's State Industries Promotion Corporation (SIPCOT) announced that it would take back 342.22 acres of land that it had given for expansion of the facility.<ref name=\"TH20180530-1\">{{cite news | title = T.N. to take back land allotted to Sterlite | newspaper = The Hindu | location = Chennai / New Delhi | language = English | publisher = The Hindu Group | date = 30 May 2018 | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/tn-to-take-back-land-allotted-to-sterlite/article24029865.ece | access-date = 30 May 2018}}</ref> Many political leaders including [[M.K.Stalin]], [[Seeman (politician)|Seeman]] and [[Anbumani Ramadoss]] criticized the sealing order, saying that it would not stand up to legal scrutiny since the government had given no reason for shutting down the factory.<ref name=\"TH20180530-2\">{{cite news | title = G.O. won't stand up to legal scrutiny: Stalin | newspaper = The Hindu | location = Chennai | language = English | publisher = The Hindu Group | date = 30 May 2018 | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/go-wont-stand-up-to-legal-scrutiny-stalin/article24027956.ece | access-date = 30 May 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"TH20180530-3\">{{cite news | title = G.O. to close Sterlite plant inadequate | newspaper = The Hindu | location = Chennai | language = English | publisher = The Hindu Group | date = 30 May 2018 | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/go-to-close-sterlite-plant-inadequate/article24030059.ece | access-date = 30 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Aftermath ==\nOn October 28, 2018, the Tamil Nadu Pollution Control Board reported that the sulphur-dioxide levels in the air had reduced significantly after the Sterlite plant's closure.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/national/so2-levels-have-reduced-significantly-after-closure-of-sterlite-plant-tnpcb/article25353938.ece|title=SO2 levels have reduced significantly after closure of Sterlite plant: TNPCB|last=Simhan|first=TE Raja|website=@businessline|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\nOn November 2019, the Tamil Nadu Pollution Control Board reported that the [[Ambient air quality criteria|ambient air quality]] had improved dramatically after the closure of the plant.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/environment/tuticorin-air-quality-aqi-sterlite-copper-smelting-pollution-sipcot-tnpcb|title=Tuticorin Air Quality Improves Noticeably After Sterlite Closure: TNPCB Data|website=The Wire|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Manjolai Labourers massacre]]\n* [[2018 Tamil Nadu protests for Kaveri water sharing]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Pollution in India]]\n[[Category:Police brutality in India]]\n[[Category:2018 in Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:2018 murders in Asia]]\n[[Category:May 2018 crimes in Asia|Thoothukudi_firing]]\n[[Category:Thoothukudi]]\n[[Category:Protests in India]]\n", "name_user": "Arjayay", "label": "safe", "comment": "Duplicate word removed", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thoothukudi_massacre"}
